        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(groups): use 'channel' wording in intro for ChatType channel (fixes #95645) (AI-assisted)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFor any non-DM Mattermost conversation — including a public channel — the system-prompt intro declares *\"You are in a `<provider>` group chat.\"* even when `ChatType` is `\"channel\"`. This contradicts the authoritative inbound-meta block which reports `chat_type: \"channel\"`, causing agents to misidentify public channels as group chats and emit the wrong `chat_type` in tool arguments.\n\n## What does this PR do?\n\nUses the actual `ChatType` value to pick `\"channel\"` or `\"group chat\"` in the intro line rendered by `buildGroupChatContext`.\n\n## Related Issue\n\nFixes #95645\n\n## Type of Change\n\n- [x] Bug fix (non-breaking)\n- [x] AI-assisted (Hermes Agent)\n\n## Changes Made\n\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/groups.ts`: Added `chatTypeLabel` ternary that renders \"channel\" when `ChatType === \"channel\"`, \"group chat\" otherwise. Interpolated into the intro line.\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/groups.test.ts`: Added test verifying correct wording for both `ChatType: \"channel\"` and `ChatType: \"group\"`.\n\n## How to Test\n\n1. `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/auto-reply/reply/groups.test.ts` — all 7 verifications pass\n2. `grep -n 'chatTypeLabel' src/auto-reply/reply/groups.ts` — confirms the ternary at line 242\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** The intro prose in `buildGroupChatContext` unconditionally rendered \"group chat\" for all non-DM conversations, including public channels where `ChatType` is `\"channel\"`.\n- **Real environment tested:** macOS, Node 22, upstream/main at `e9be15ff`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after the patch:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/auto-reply/reply/groups.test.ts\n ✓  auto-reply  src/auto-reply/reply/groups.test.ts (7 tests) 111ms\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  7 passed (7)\n```\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n```\n$ grep -n 'chatTypeLabel' src/auto-reply/reply/groups.ts\n242:  const chatTypeLabel = params.sessionCtx.ChatType === \"channel\" ? \"channel\" : \"group chat\";\n244:  lines.push(`You are in a ${providerLabel} ${chatTypeLabel}.`);\n\n$ node -e \"const fs=require('fs'); const s=fs.readFileSync('src/auto-reply/reply/groups.ts','utf8'); console.log('Has ChatType ternary:', s.includes('ChatType === \\\"channel\\\" ? \\\"channel\\\" : \\\"group chat\\\"')); console.log('Has interpolation:', s.includes('\\${chatTypeLabel}'));\"\nHas ChatType ternary: true\nHas interpolation: true\n```\n- **Observed result after fix:** When `ChatType` is `\"channel\"`, the intro now renders *\"You are in a Mattermost channel.\"* instead of *\"You are in a Mattermost group chat.\"*. When `ChatType` is `\"group\"`, it still renders *\"You are in a Mattermost group chat.\"* as before.\n- **What was not tested:** Live Mattermost channel interaction (the change is a string interpolation in a pure function; the verification suite covers both code paths).\n\n## Checklist\n\n- [x] Read Contributing Guide\n- [x] Conventional Commits\n- [x] Searched for duplicates\n- [x] Only related changes\n- [x] Verification pass\n- [x] Added regression coverage\n- [x] Did NOT edit CHANGELOG.md\n- [x] AI-assisted disclosure included\n",
        "branch": "fix/mattermost-channel-intro-wording",
